    <h2>ULEZ</h2>

<p>Every year thousands of Londoners die early from being exposed to polluted air, and almost a quarter of London schools are in areas which don't meet legal air quality limits. Around 50% of this pollution comes from road vehicles.</p>

<p>The ULEZ was created to help reduce deadly vehicle emissions and make London a safer and more pleasant place to live.</p>

<p>The ULEZ will operate&nbsp;<strong>24 hours a day, 7 days a week, every day of the year</strong>&nbsp;within the same area of central London as the Congestion Charge. When it launches&nbsp;on Monday 8 April 2019 you'll be able to:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Pay Congestion Charge and ULEZ and Low Emission Zone (LEZ) charges online in a single tool</li>
	<li>Pay all charges, including penalty charges through the new TfL Pay to drive in London app</li>
	<li>Check if your vehicle meets ULEZ and/or LEZ emissions standards through a single, combined tool</li>
</ul>

<p>Until then you can use the separate vehicle checkers.</p>
