<p>If you drive within the ULEZ zone and your vehicle doesn't meet the emissions standards, you will need to pay:</p>

<ul>
	<li>&pound;12.50 for most vehicle types, including cars, motorcycles and vans (up to and including 3.5 tonnes)</li>
	<li>&pound;100 for heavier vehicles, including lorries (over 3.5 tonnes) and buses/coaches (over 5 tonnes)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Congestion Charge</h2>

<p>The Congestion Charge operates in central London between 07:00 and 18:00, Monday to Friday. The daily charge for driving within the zone is &pound;11.50.</p>

<h2>LEZ</h2>

<p>The LEZ&nbsp;covers most of Greater London and operates 24 hours a day, every day of the year, midnight to midnight. If you drive within the LEZ between 23:30 and 01:00 the next day, you need to pay for two days.&nbsp;</p>

<p>The daily charge is &pound;100 for larger vans, minibuses and other specialist vehicles, and &pound;200 for lorries, buses, coaches and other specialist heavy vehicles.</p>
